{"title_page": "List of certified songs in South Korea", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikimedia list article}}\n{{Complete list|date=December 2019}}\n[[File:Gaon Music Chart.png|thumb|200px|Logo of the [[Gaon Music Chart]], introduced in 2010|alt=The Logo of the Gaon Music Chart]]\n[[File:\ub124\ud30c \ub530\ub73b\ud55c \uc138\uc0c1 \ucea0\ud398\uc778 \ub860\uce6d \ubc1c\ud45c\ud68c (IKON).jpg|thumb|200px|[[iKon]]'s ''(pictured in 2015)'' \"[[Love Scenario]]\" was the first song to be certified platinum for 100 million streams in June and for 2.5 million downloads in November 2018.|alt=South Korean boy band iKon in 2015]]\n[[File:\ubaa8\ubaa8\ub79c\ub4dc 180223 KBS \ubba4\uc9c1\ubc45\ud06c \ucd9c\uadfc\uae38 (cropped).png|200px|thumb|[[Momoland]] ''(pictured in 2017)'' was the first female act to be certified for their song \"[[Bboom Bboom]]\" in August 2018.]] \n[[File:(\uc9c1\ucea0)(4K 60P) \ud3f4\ud0b4 - \ucee4\ud53c \ud55c \uc794 \ud560\ub798\uc694 (180415 2018 H.A.N.D \ud398\uc2a4\ud2f0\ubc8c) by.JAS 23s.jpg|thumb|200px|[[Paul Kim (musician, born 1988)|Paul Kim]]'s \"Every Day, Every Moment\" became the first song to be certified 2 \u00d7 Platinum for 200 million streams in July 2019.|alt=Paul Kim in 2018]]\n[[File:\u2018LG Q7 BTS \uc5d0\ub514\uc158\u2019 \uc608\uc57d \ud310\ub9e4 \uc2dc\uc791 (42773472410) (cropped).jpg|thumb|200px|[[Ben (South Korean singer)|Ben]], [[BTS (band)|BTS]] ''(pictured in 2018)'', [[Paul Kim (musician, born 1988)|Paul Kim]], [[Chungha |Chungha]],[[Twice (group)|Twice]] and [[Blackpink|BLACKPINK]] only artists who have two or more certified songs.]]\n[[File:Anne-Marie Rose Nicholson, 2017 (cropped).jpg|thumb|200px|[[Anne-Marie (singer)|Anne-Marie]]'s ''(pictured in 2017)'' \"[[2002 (song)|2002]]\" was the first non-Korean language song to be certified.]]\nSince 2018, 39 songs, 38 for streaming and 18 for downloads as well, have been certified in [[South Korea]] in accordance with the certification levels set up by the [[Gaon Music Chart|Korea Music Content Association]] (KMCA). Established in 2008, the KMCA introduced the official South Korean charts in 2010<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/news/art/2010/06/201_61266.html |title=Korea Launches First Official Music Charts Gaon |author=Han, Sang-hee |date=23 February 2010 |accessdate=November 11, 2018 |work=The Korea Times  |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100804044458/http://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/news/art/2010/06/201_61266.html |archivedate=August 4, 2010}}</ref> and record certifications were implemented in April 2018.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://k-mca.or.kr/board/board.php?bo_table=media&idx=372 |title={{bracket|\ud55c\uad6d\uc74c\uc545\ucf58\ud150\uce20\ud611\ud68c}} (\uc0ac)\ud55c\uad6d\uc74c\uc545\ucf58\ud150\uce20\ud611\ud68c, \uc74c\uc6d0\u2219\uc568\ubc94\uc5d0 \ub300\ud55c \u2018\uac00\uc628 \uc778\uc99d\uc81c\u2019 \uc2dc\ud589 |trans-title=[Korea Music Content Association] Korea Music Contents Association, 'Gaon Accreditation System' for songs and albums |date=April 23, 2018 |accessdate=November 11, 2018 |publisher=Korea Music Content Association |language=Korean |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181111055754/http://k-mca.or.kr/board/board.php?bo_table=media&idx=372 |archivedate=November 11, 2018}}</ref> Every song released after January 1, 2018 is eligible for a certification. The KMCA divides certification for songs in streaming and downloads.\n\nThe first song to be certified platinum for streams and downloads was [[iKon]]'s \"[[Love Scenario]]\" in June and November 2018.\n\n==Certification levels==\n{|class=wikitable\n!colspan=\"4\"|Thresholds per award\n|-\n!colspan=\"4\"|Streaming\n|-\n!Platinum\n!2\u00d7 Platinum\n!3\u00d7{{nbsp}}Platinum{{efn|Higher certifications (up to 9\u00d7 Platinum) will also be awarded.}}\n!Billion\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center; width=\"80\"|100,000,000\n|style=\"text-align:center; width=\"80\"|200,000,000\n|style=\"text-align:center; width=\"80\"|300,000,000\n|style=\"text-align:center; width=\"80\"|1,000,000,000\n|-\n!colspan=\"4\"|Download\n|-\n!Platinum\n!2\u00d7 Platinum\n!3\u00d7 Platinum\n!Diamond\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center; width=\"80\"|2,500,000\n|style=\"text-align:center; width=\"80\"|5,000,000\n|style=\"text-align:center; width=\"80\"|7,500,000\n|style=\"text-align:center; width=\"80\"|10,000,000\n|}\n\n==By downloads/streams==\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n|-\n!scope=col rowspan=\"2\" class=\"sortable\"|Song\n!scope=col rowspan=\"2\" class=\"sortable\"|Artist(s)\n!scope=col colspan=\"2\" class=\"sortable\"|Certification\n!scope=col rowspan=\"2\" class=\"sortable\"|Release Date\n!scope=col colspan=\"2\" class=\"sortable\"|Certification Date\n!scope=col rowspan=\"2\" class=\"sortable\"|Certified<br />Streams\n!scope=col rowspan=\"2\" class=\"sortable\"|Certified<br />Sales\n|-\n!Streaming\n!Download\n!Streaming<ref>{{cite web |url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/certification/list.gaon?serviceGbn=S1040 |title=\uac00\uc628 \uc778\uc99d: \ub204\uc801\uc0ac\uc6a9\ub7c9 \uc778\uc99d |trans-title=Gaon Certification: Streaming |work=[[Gaon Music Chart]] |publisher=Korea Music Content Association |language=ko |accessdate=March 7, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181108105238/http://www.gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/certification/list.gaon?serviceGbn=S1040 |archive-date=November 8, 2018 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n!Download<ref>{{cite web |url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/certification/list.gaon?serviceGbn=S1040 |title=\uac00\uc628 \uc778\uc99d: \ub204\uc801\ud310\ub9e4\ub7c9 \uc778\uc99d |trans-title=Gaon Certification: Download |work=[[Gaon Music Chart]] |publisher=Korea Music Content Association |language=ko |accessdate=April 11, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181108105238/http://www.gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/certification/list.gaon?serviceGbn=S1040 |archive-date=November 8, 2018 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n|